{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 21:14:39.013776", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and Topology\\n- SDN spine–leaf: leaf_1, leaf_2 (OVS) connected to spine_1 (OVS).\\n- Hosts: host_1_1 (10.0.0.1) and host_1_2 (10.0.0.2) on leaf_1; host_2_1 (10.0.0.5) and host_2_2 (10.0.0.6) on leaf_2.\\n- Controller at 20.0.0.100 via OpenFlow; all switches in fail_mode: secure.\\n\\nKey Findings and Evidence\\n\\n1) End-to-end reachability\\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1.\\n- host_1_1 -> host_2_1 and -> host_2_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1.\\n- host_2_1 <-> host_2_2: ping attempts timed out via tool; ARP state indicates partial communication (see ARP below).\\n\\n2) Host network configuration (interfaces/routes)\\n- All hosts have eth0 UP with expected /24 addressing and on-link route:\\n  - host_1_1: 10.0.0.1/24\\n  - host_1_2: 10.0.0.2/24\\n  - host_2_1: 10.0.0.5/24\\n  - host_2_2: 10.0.0.6/24\\n- No host-side misconfigurations detected.\\n\\n3) ARP/Neighbor state\\n- host_1_1: all neighbors (10.0.0.2/.5/.6 etc.) FAILED — ARP not resolving at all behind leaf_1.\\n- host_1_2: neighbors FAILED.\\n- host_2_1: 10.0.0.6 (peer) in DELAY; 10.0.0.8 in REACHABLE; others FAILED — indicates some L2/L3 traffic transiting leaf_2.\\n- host_2_2: 10.0.0.5 (peer) STALE; 10.0.0.8 REACHABLE — again suggests leaf_2 is forwarding at least to some destinations.\\n\\n4) Switch controller connectivity and port states\\n- All switches report controller \"is_connected: true\".\\n- Port states on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: all relevant eth ports are LIVE with 10Gb-FD; LOCAL port shows LINK_DOWN, which is expected for the internal interface and not indicative of dataplane link issues.\\n\\n5) OpenFlow pipeline state (critical)\\n- leaf_1 (OVS):\\n  - Table 0 has a single rule: priority=100 actions=drop (no other flows).\\n  - This effectively drops all traffic — including ARP — in secure fail mode.\\n- leaf_2 (OVS):\\n  - Numerous flows present in table 0, including specific dl_dst entries for host MACs mapping to correct output ports (evidence of active controller programming).\\n- spine_1 (OVS):\\n  - Numerous flows present, showing active programming.\\n\\nAssessment of Network Health\\n- Severe impairment isolated to all traffic traversing leaf_1: complete L2 failure (no ARP, no intra-leaf host-to-host connectivity).\\n- Leaf_2 and spine_1 appear to be programmed and forwarding, as indicated by populated flow tables and ARP activity on hosts connected to leaf_2.\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n- leaf_1 is operating with only a default drop rule in table 0. No forwarding entries exist.\\n- Hosts on leaf_1 cannot resolve ARP to any peers, including same-leaf peer (host_1_2), consistent with a drop-all pipeline.\\n- Contrastingly, leaf_2 and spine_1 have extensive flow entries, suggesting normal controller programming there.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Fault localized to leaf_1’s OpenFlow pipeline configuration and/or its interaction with the controller.\\n- Physical links and host NIC configs are healthy; issue is not host-side.\\n- Controller connectivity flag is “true” for leaf_1, so the dataplane failure is due to missing/incorrect flow programming on leaf_1 rather than an OVS–controller transport loss.\\n\\nRoot Cause Hypothesis\\n- Controller is not programming leaf_1 (no flow_mods received/applied), leaving the switch with only a default drop behavior in secure mode.\\n- Potential reasons (based on evidence):\\n  - The controller’s application/pipeline does not recognize/program leaf_1 (e.g., mismatch in expected DPID/pipeline or policy excluding this device).\\n  - Leaf_1 may have been left in a “default drop” state awaiting pipeline setup that never occurred.\\n  - Less likely: flow programming attempted but failed only on leaf_1 (e.g., controller sending flows incompatible with leaf_1 pipeline), though controller shows “connected”.\\n\\nSummary\\n- Abnormal behavior: Complete forwarding blackout on leaf_1 due to only a drop-all rule installed; hosts on leaf_1 have no ARP or L2 connectivity (even intra-leaf).\\n- Normal behavior elsewhere: leaf_2 and spine_1 are correctly programmed and show signs of forwarding.\\n- Faulty device: leaf_1 (control-plane/pipeline state).\\n- Root cause: Controller flow programming failure specific to leaf_1, resulting in a default drop pipeline in secure fail mode., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a0e1030b-e173-4c09-b4e7-8706b208c1ba'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
